[4] Pennsylvania (Lancaster County)
Date: Sat 21 Dec 2013
Source: Lancaster Online [edited]
http://lancasteronline.com/article/local/934371_4-whooping-cough-cases-in-Pequea-Valley-schools.html


For the 2nd time in a month, a Lancaster County school district is experiencing an outbreak of whooping cough.

Pequea Valley School District has 4 confirmed cases of the illness, explained a letter written to parents and guardians from Superintendent Erik Orndorff, who could not be reached for comment on Saturday [21 Dec 2013]. The district's website, http://www.pvsd.k12.pa.us, includes a notice on the outbreak as well.

In November 2013, Penn Manor School District had 3 cases of the infection. The CDC website said there were 1945 confirmed cases of pertussis in Pennsylvania last year [2012] and 48 277 nationwide.

[Byline: Paula Wolf]

